<!-- NFOWORKS.ORG PURSUING HARMONY BLOGGER TEMPLATE REVISION HISTORY
     0.15 2010-04-17T03:04Z Reduce differences, synchronizing here and =
Orcmid's Lair, getting the fonts right.
     0.14 2010-04-16T02:51Z I fixed the alignment of the blog body with =
respect to the sidebar, I think.
     0.13 2010-04-16T02:33Z Work up shading for sidebar, title block, =
and bottom block.  Get the text fonts
          the way I want.
     0.12 2010-04-15T00:42Z Add Attribution Link to the Title Blocks
     0.11 2010-04-11T18:07Z ADD CREATIVE COMMONS LICENSE TO BOTTOM BLOCK
          Remove the orcmid link to get more room
     0.10 2010-04-11T02:59Z REPAIR THE TITLE BLOCK (Partial)
          I am adjusting the nfoWorks and Pursuing Harmony titles and =
also repairing the shading a little to
          see what the dependencies are.
     0.09 2010-04-11T02:07Z START MAJOR REDESIGN OF THE BLOG TEMPLATE =
STARTED
          I am going to mimic the basic design structure of Orcmid's =
Lair default.asp.template 0.39.  The first
          changes involve simplifying the CSS styles at the top and then =
adding a table structure that I roll
          the material into until I have a new, fully-working template.  =
This version will be for content.
          Then I get to tweak appearance.
     0.08 2010-01-26T01:25Z Remove About Me block
     0.07 2010-01-26T00:55Z Rearrange Left Sidebar
          I am changing the order of things to have the same sequence as =
the latest Orcmid's Lair template.
          I will see if it works to also use the same styling.
     0.06 2010-01-02T01:52Z Correct Styles, Layout and Sidebar
          The Atom Feed links are repaired with absolute links to the =
correct feed location
          The title links are divided, hover is made red, and the title =
is lightened and italicized.
          The blog date header is turned into a link.
          I worked on the line-height a bit.
     0.05 2008-08-21T00:32Z Improve Styles and Layout
          Links are changed to bold, with no underlining.  Adjust =
spacing on sidebar.  Remove stray link at=20
          end of posts.
     0.04 2008-08-20T23:43Z Enrich the Sidebar
          Unify the font colors and weights on the sidebar, matching the =
body styles. Rearrange sidebar but keep
          Blogger Profile item until blog is claimed on Technorati. =20
     0.03 2008-08-17T16:13Z Additional Clean-Ups
          The title is centered in its block at the top of pages, the =
entire sidebar is right-justified, and the=20
          blog description is changed to italic with not such a large =
indentation.
     0.02 2008-08-16T16:53Z Make Simple Clean-Ups
          I corrected a doubling of "Jason" and a missing ":" in the =
version-control $Header label in the introductory
          template comment.  I deleted the only JavaScript in the =
template as completely unnecessary and made the
          title always link to the main page from all blog pages, =
including the main page.  I did some adjusting on
          how links appear and using the body tag to control it.  =
Finally, I am moving the description to the sidebar
          and then right-justifying everything below the profile.  The =
Blogger badge move and I get rid of the bogus
          links in the sidebar for now.
     0.01 2008-08-14T00:55Z Provide Basic Formatting Control
          The !DOCTYPE is added to the front of the file.  The version =
control header is added in the introductory
          comment before the <head> element.  This revision history is =
"primed" with this entry and identification
          of the original download capture.  This version is uploaded as =
the new template to confirm that there
          is no disruption.
     0.00 2008-08-13T23:41 Capture Template as Backup from Blogger
          The Blogger template on the Blogger dashboard is captured in a =
text file and imported into the site at
          http://nfoWorks.org/diary/default.htm.template.txt.  From now =
on, revisions of this file will be loaded
          from here into the Blogger template by copy and paste.
